<title type="html"><![CDATA[6/2(Sat.)7 Ways to Live a Simpler Life in a Modern World &amp; dementia (Host: Krista)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=174&amp;p=188#p188"><![CDATA[
7 Ways to Live a Simpler Life in a Modern World<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.becomingminimalist.com/simpler/">https://www.becomingminimalist.com/simpler/</a><!-- m --><br />1. How is your life? Simple or complex? <br />2. Are you happy with your current life situation? Why or why not?<br />3. What can you live without?<br />4. Discuss each method of living a simpler life in this article, and give your opinion.<br />5. What does simple living really mean to you?<br /><br />Inside the Dutch 'dementia village' that offers beer, bingo, and top-notch healthcare<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.businessinsider.com/inside-hogewey-dementia-village-2017-7">http://www.businessinsider.com/inside-h ... age-2017-7</a><!-- m --><br />1. If you have dementia, would you willing to live in the dementia village? or your parents have dementia, would you willing to send your parents to dementia village?<br />2. What the difference between Alzheimer’s and dementia is?<br />3. Do you consider how old is old?<br />4. Do you have any elder family member? How is his/her quality of life? <br />5. Do you think how to improve the quality of life for seniors?<br /><br />Saturday's meeting place:<br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven, <br />板橋民生路二段237 號, <br />tel: 2255-8132<br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30, <br />minimum charge of Dante coffee for Royal English club attendant NT$80 (丹提低消80元)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.請帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=872">Shuman</a> — Wed May 30, 2018 11:04 pm</p><hr />
